21/01/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- US Undersecretary of State for Political Affairs Nicholas Burns reaffirmed Washington's commitment to the fight against the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK), during his visit to Ankara on January 19th-20th. 
He was in the Turkish capital as part of a regional tour that also includes Israel and the United Arab Emirates. 
Following talks with senior Turkish officials, including Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan, Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul and National Security Council Secretary General Yigit Alpogan, Burns vowed "serious efforts" to oust the PKK. 
He reiterated the US view that the problem could be largely resolved via collaboration between Turkey, the United States and Iraq. 
(Zaman, TurkishPress.com, AFP - 20/01/07)
